---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Scoring Guide — Points & Values"
  description="Complete Scrabble scoring guide: every letter value, premium square multipliers, the 50-point bingo bonus, and worked examples. Free reference."
  keywords="scrabble scoring, scrabble letter values, scrabble points, scrabble tile values, scrabble score calculator, bingo bonus scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Scrabble Scoring Guide: Letter Values, Premium Squares & Bonus Points",
    "description": "Complete Scrabble scoring guide: every letter value, premium square multipliers, the 50-point bingo bonus, and worked examples.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-12",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-scoring-guide" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How much is each letter worth in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Letter values range from 1 to 10 points. Common letters (E, A, I, O, N, R, T, L, S, U) are worth 1 point. Mid-frequency letters (D, G) are 2 points, (B, C, M, P) are 3 points, (F, H, V, W, Y) are 4 points. K is 5, (J, X) are 8 points, and (Q, Z) are 10 points. Blanks are worth 0." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the 50-point bonus in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "The 50-point bonus (called a 'bingo') is awarded when a player uses all 7 tiles from their rack in a single turn. The bonus is added after all premium square multipliers are applied." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Do premium squares apply every turn in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "No. Premium squares (double letter, triple letter, double word, triple word) only apply on the turn a tile is first placed on them. Once covered, they have no effect on subsequent words that include that tile." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Scoring</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Scoring Guide: Letter Values, Premium Squares & Bonus Points</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-12">June 12, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        Scoring in Scrabble goes beyond just knowing words — it's about maximising the value of every tile you place. This guide covers every letter value, explains how premium squares multiply your score, breaks down the 50-point bingo bonus, and walks through real scoring examples so you can calculate with confidence.
      </p>

      <!-- Hero Card -->
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">🏆 Master Scoring</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">EVERY POINT COUNTS</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">187 total tile points • 61 premium squares • 50-point bingo bonus</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">The difference between average and expert players isn't vocabulary — it's knowing exactly how to maximise score from every tile placement.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Stat Strip -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-400">187</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Total tile points</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-400">10</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Max letter value</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-400">61</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Premium squares</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-400">+50</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Bingo bonus</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Letter Values: The Complete List</h2>
      <p>Every tile in Scrabble has a fixed point value based on how frequently that letter appears in English. Common letters score low, rare letters score high:</p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
          <thead class="bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Points</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Letters</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Tiles in Bag</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">0</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">Blank (wildcard)</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">2</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">1</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">E, A, I, O, N, R, T, L, S, U</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">E×12, A×9, I×9, O×8, N×6, R×6, T×6, L×4, S×4, U×4</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">2</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">D, G</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">D×4, G×3</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">B, C, M, P</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">B×2, C×2, M×2, P×2</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">F, H, V, W, Y</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">F×2, H×2, V×2, W×2, Y×2</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">K</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">K×1</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">J, X</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">J×1, X×1</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">Q, Z</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">Q×1, Z×1</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <p>The total of all tiles in the bag is 187 points. Our <a href="/" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">free word finder</a> shows the score for every word it finds automatically — no manual calculation needed.</p>

      <!-- Insight callout -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Scoring Pattern</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">The 10 one-point letters (E, A, I, O, N, R, T, L, S, U) make up <span class="text-white font-medium">68 of 100 tiles</span> — over two-thirds of the bag. High-value letters are rare but game-changing when placed on premium squares.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Pill badges: high-value letters -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">Q</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">10 pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">Z</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">10 pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">J</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">8 pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">X</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">8 pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">K</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">5 pts</span>
        </span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Premium Squares</h2>
      <p>The board contains 61 coloured premium squares that multiply your score. They come in four types:</p>

      <!-- Card grid: premium square types -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/10">
          <p class="text-blue-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🟦 Double Letter (DL)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Doubles the value of one tile. <strong class="text-white">24 on the board.</strong></p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-950/10">
          <p class="text-indigo-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🟪 Triple Letter (TL)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Triples the value of one tile. <strong class="text-white">12 on the board.</strong></p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-pink-500/30 bg-pink-950/10">
          <p class="text-pink-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🩷 Double Word (DW)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Doubles entire word score. <strong class="text-white">17 on the board</strong> (incl. centre star).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🟥 Triple Word (TW)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Triples entire word score. <strong class="text-white">8 on the board.</strong></p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Double Letter Score (DL):</strong> Light blue squares. Doubles the point value of the single tile placed on it. 24 on the board.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Triple Letter Score (TL):</strong> Dark blue squares. Triples the point value of the single tile placed on it. 12 on the board.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Double Word Score (DW):</strong> Pink squares. Doubles the entire word's score after all letter multipliers. 16 on the board (plus the centre star).</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Triple Word Score (TW):</strong> Red squares. Triples the entire word's score after all letter multipliers. 8 on the board.</span></li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Warning callout -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-amber-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">⚠️ One-Time Only</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Premium squares only apply on the turn a tile is <span class="text-white font-medium">first placed</span> on them. Once covered, they have no effect on subsequent words that include that tile.</p>
      </div>

      <p>For strategies on using these effectively, see our <a href="/blog/understanding-premium-squares/" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">premium squares strategy guide</a>.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">How Scoring Works Step by Step</h2>
      <p>When calculating the score for a word, follow this exact order:</p>

      <!-- Numbered Steps -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-purple-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">🧩 Scoring Sequence</p>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">1</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">Write down the face value of each tile in the word</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">2</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">Apply letter multipliers (DL ×2, TL ×3) to newly placed tiles on those squares</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">3</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">Sum all tile values (after letter multipliers applied)</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">4</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">Apply word multipliers (DW ×2, TW ×3) — multiply the total</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">5</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">If multiple word multipliers apply, multiply sequentially (DW × DW = ×4)</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Scoring Examples</h2>

      <!-- Scoring examples as card grid -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">Example 1: Simple Word</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mb-1">QUIZ — no premium squares</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-white font-bold">Q(10) + U(1) + I(1) + Z(10) = 22 pts</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">Example 2: Letter Multiplier</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mb-1">JAZZ — J on Double Letter</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-white font-bold">J(8×2) + A(1) + Z(10) + Z(10) = 37 pts</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">Example 3: Word Multiplier</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mb-1">ZONE — Z on Triple Word</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-white font-bold">(10+1+1+1) × 3 = 39 pts</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">Example 4: Combined</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mb-1">QUIX — Q on TL, X on DW</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-white font-bold">(30+1+1+8) × 2 = 80 pts</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">Example 1: Simple Word</h3>
      <p>Playing <strong>QUIZ</strong> with no premium squares:</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Q(10) + U(1) + I(1) + Z(10) = <strong>22 points</strong></p>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">Example 2: With Letter Multiplier</h3>
      <p>Playing <strong>JAZZ</strong> with the J on a Double Letter square:</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">J(8×2=16) + A(1) + Z(10) + Z(10) = <strong>37 points</strong></p>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">Example 3: With Word Multiplier</h3>
      <p>Playing <strong>ZONE</strong> with the Z landing on a Triple Word square:</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">(Z(10) + O(1) + N(1) + E(1)) × 3 = 13 × 3 = <strong>39 points</strong></p>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">Example 4: Letter + Word Multiplier Combined</h3>
      <p>Playing <strong>QUIX</strong> with Q on Triple Letter and X on Double Word:</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">(Q(10×3=30) + U(1) + I(1) + X(8)) × 2 = 40 × 2 = <strong>80 points</strong></p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">The 50-Point Bingo Bonus</h2>
      <p>One of the most exciting moments in Scrabble is achieving a "bingo" — playing all 7 tiles from your rack in a single turn. This earns a flat 50-point bonus added after all premium square calculations.</p>

      <!-- Green callout -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-green-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">🎯 Bingo Math</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">A 7-tile word scoring 24 after multipliers = <span class="text-white font-medium">24 + 50 = 74 points</span>. On a Triple Word square: <span class="text-white font-medium">(24 × 3) + 50 = 122 points</span>. The bonus is always added last.</p>
      </div>

      <p>For example, if your 7-tile word scores 24 points after multipliers, your total for that turn would be 24 + 50 = <strong>74 points</strong>. If it lands on a Triple Word square: (24 × 3) + 50 = <strong>122 points</strong>.</p>
      <p>Competitive players actively manage their racks to maximise bingo chances. Common bingo-friendly letter combinations include -ING, -TION, -NESS, and RE-. Our word finder can help you spot bingo opportunities instantly — just enter all 7 tiles and look for 7-letter results.</p>

      <!-- Pill badges: bingo-friendly combos -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">-ING</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">suffix</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">-TION</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">suffix</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">-NESS</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">suffix</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">RE-</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">prefix</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">UN-</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">prefix</span>
        </span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Multiple Words in One Turn</h2>
      <p>When your play creates multiple words simultaneously (by building parallel to an existing word), you score each word separately. The premium square bonuses apply to every word that uses the newly placed tile. This is one of the most powerful scoring techniques — a single tile can earn points in two or three words at once.</p>

      <!-- Insight callout -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Parallel Play Power</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">A premium square bonus applies to <span class="text-white font-medium">every word</span> that uses the newly placed tile. Creating 2-3 words simultaneously often outscores one long word by 2-3× the points.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Inline cross-links -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-indigo-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">📚 Dig Deeper</p>
        <div class="grid gap-2">
          <a href="/blog/understanding-premium-squares/" class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-900/20 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-indigo-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform shrink-0">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-indigo-300 transition-colors">Understanding Premium Squares — maximize every DL, TL, DW, TW</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-rules-explained/" class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-900/20 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-indigo-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform shrink-0">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-indigo-300 transition-colors">Scrabble Rules Explained — complete legal play reference</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Endgame Scoring Adjustments</h2>
      <p>When the game ends:</p>

      <!-- Comparison cards: endgame scenarios -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Player Who Goes Out</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Adds the combined value of all opponents' remaining tiles to their own score. Double advantage.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ Players With Tiles Left</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Subtract the total face value of their remaining rack tiles from their score.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span>Each player subtracts the total face value of tiles remaining on their rack</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span>The player who goes out (empties their rack) adds the combined value of all opponents' remaining tiles to their own score</span></li>
      </ul>
      <p>This means going out first is a double advantage: you avoid subtraction and gain a bonus. In close games, this can swing the result by 20-30 points.</p>

